Goldcorp Secures Approval for First Chile Gold Mine, DF Reports

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-03-15T11:35:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/goldcorp-secures-approval-for-first-chile-gold-mine-df-reports.html
Canada’s  Goldcorp Inc. (G)  received
approval from environmental authorities in  Chile  to build its
first gold mine in the country, Diario Financiero reported.  The $2.5 billion El Morro mine would produce 60,000 ounces
of gold and 200,000 metric tons of copper a year, the Santiago-
based newspaper reported, citing the Atacama region’s
environmental evaluation commission.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  